Description of the eggs. The eggs, laid freely, were spherical with long conical processes (
Fig. 4 A, B
); we were only able to measure one egg, which had a diameter of 87 µm, excluding the processes, 123 µm including; the processes, 30 around the circumference and about 120 in the hemisphere, were conical, long and flexible, 18.2– 18.6 µm tall, with basal diameter of 6.1–6.3 long µm.
